<item>
            <title>[SPARK-5416] Initialize Executor.threadPool before ExecutorSource</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-5416</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I recently saw some NPEs from &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/0497ea51ac345f8057d222a18dbbf8eae78f5b92/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/executor/ExecutorSource.scala#L44&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ExecutorSource:44&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in the first couple seconds of my executors&apos; being initialized.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think that &lt;tt&gt;ExecutorSource&lt;/tt&gt; was trying to report these metrics before its threadpool was initialized; there are a few LoC between the source being registered (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/0497ea51ac345f8057d222a18dbbf8eae78f5b92/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/executor/Executor.scala#L82&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Executor.scala:82&lt;/a&gt;) and the threadpool being initialized (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/0497ea51ac345f8057d222a18dbbf8eae78f5b92/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/executor/Executor.scala#L106&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Executor.scala:106&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should initialize the threapool before the ExecutorSource is registered.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
